Source: gvm-libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Mohammad Razavi <mrazavi64@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 12), cmake, pkg-config, libglib2.0-dev, libgnutls28-dev, libgcrypt20-dev, zlib1g-dev, libgpgme-dev, uuid-dev, libssh-dev, libhiredis-dev, libldap2-dev, libradcli-dev, libfreeradius-dev, libxml2-dev, libpcap-dev, doxygen, xmltoman
Standards-Version: 4.4.1
Section: libs
Homepage: https://community.greenbone.net/
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/greenbone/gvm-libs
Vcs-git: https://github.com/greenbone/gvm-libs.git

Package: libgvm-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libgvm (= ${binary:Version}), uuid-dev
Description: remote network security auditor - static libraries and headers
 The Greenbone Vulnerability Management Solution (previously known as
 Open Vulnerability Assessment System) is a modular security auditing tool,
 used for testing remote systems for vulnerabilities that should be fixed.
 .
 It is made up of several parts: a manager i.e. the main server gvmd.
 A scanner openvas-scanner that execute vulnerability checking scripts.
 A  web interface called Greenbone Security Assistant gsad.
 .
 This package contains the required static libraries and headers.

